The paper discusses the creation of a new dataset for macro-management in StarCraft II, which involves using machine learning algorithms to make decisions about resource management, unit production, and other high-level strategies. This falls under the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of computer vision techniques for feature extraction (cs.CV) and game theory for decision-making (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses natural language processing for parsing and preprocessing the dataset (cs.CL).
